
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class University {
  -faculties: List<Faculty>
  -totalEmployees: int
}

class Faculty {
  -name: String
  -institutes: List<Institute>
  -dean: Dean
}

class Institute {
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class Dean {
  -socialSecurityNumber: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
}

class Employee {
  -socialSecurityNumber: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
}

class ResearchAssistant <|-- Employee {
  -researchField: String
  -projects: List<Project>
}

class Project {
  -name: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -hours: int
}

class Lecturer <|-- ResearchAssistant {
  -coursesTaught: List<Course>
}

class Course {
  -courseID: String
  -name: String
  -weeklyDuration: int
}

class AdministrativeStaff <|-- Employee {
  // No specific attributes mentioned
}

University "1" *-- "0..*" Faculty
Faculty "1" *-- "0..*" Institute
Faculty "1" -- "1" Dean
Employee "1" *-- "0..*" ResearchAssistant
Employee "1" *-- "0..*" AdministrativeStaff
ResearchAssistant "1" *-- "0..*" Project
ResearchAssistant "1" *-- "0..*" Lecturer
Lecturer "1" *-- "0..*" Course
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- `University` contains multiple `Faculty` instances.
- Each `Faculty` has a name and contains multiple `Institute`s.
- Each `Faculty` has one `Dean`, who is an `Employee`.
- `Employee` is a base class for both `ResearchAssistant` and `AdministrativeStaff`.
- `ResearchAssistant` can be assigned to multiple `Project`s, and may also teach `Course`s (as a `Lecturer`).
- `Course` has a unique ID, name, and weekly duration.

